<h2>COMMON FAILURE MODES</h2>
<ul>
<li>Stating week names or time deltas from memory → compute them</li>
<li>Saying "I don't have DC" without running get_config</li>
<li>Trusting The Board without cross-checking U2</li>
<li>Living Map untouched for 20 minutes</li>
<li>Starting work before STORY is complete</li>
<li>Splitting SHEET and Living Map commits</li>
</ul>
<h2>THE NAVIGATION SYSTEM</h2>
<p>The NEST runs anchor-corrected dead reckoning. Internal estimator (session context) drifts without correction. External anchors — Bridge commits, DATE RULE, mantra, system clock — correct the drift. Dan is the primary Kalman filter.</p>
